Name: Seal imprint
Description: This seal imprint of beeswax, whose provenance is not known, is in the name of Khnemibre. The elder son of Ahmose-sa-Neith, director of works under Amasis, and the lady Satnefertum, he himself was chief of works under Darius I. Khnemibre is particularly known by the quarry inscriptions of the Wadi Hammamat.
